#load data

#rm(elo_teams)

elo <- read_csv("nfl_elo.csv")

#prep data
#copy and rename team1 and team2 fields so can keep them in original data 
elo_2<- elo%>%mutate(tm1=team1)%>%mutate(tm2=team2)
#reshape the data so there is one record for each team (original file is 1 per game)
elo_teams <- melt(elo_2, id=c("date", "season", "neutral", "playoff", "tm1", "tm2", "elo1_pre", "elo2_pre", "elo_prob1", "elo_prob2", "elo1_post", "elo2_post", "score1", "score2"))
#rename some fields
names(elo_teams)[names(elo_teams)=="value"] <- "teamname"
names(elo_teams)[names(elo_teams)=="date"] <- "gamedate"
names(elo_teams)[names(elo_teams)=="variable"] <-"teamtype"
#add a bunch of calculated fields
#Add decade, tiegame, winner, expected winner, Unexpected loss/win or expected outcome, 
#team probability, opponent probability, probability difference
elo_teams <-  elo_teams%>%mutate(season_decade = year(floor_date(gamedate, years(10))))%>%
  mutate(tiegame = ifelse(score1==score2, "tie", "no tie"))%>%
  mutate(winner= ifelse(score1==score2, "tie", ifelse(score1>score2, tm1, tm2)))%>%
  mutate(expectwinner = ifelse(elo_prob1>elo_prob2, tm1, tm2))%>%
  mutate(teamprobability=ifelse(teamtype=="team1", elo_prob1, elo_prob2))%>%
  mutate(oppoprobability =ifelse(teamtype=="team1", elo_prob2, elo_prob1))%>%
  mutate(difference = teamprobability-oppoprobability)%>%
  mutate(diff2 = abs(difference))%>%
  mutate(expectflag = ifelse(diff2<=.05, "too close", ifelse(teamname==expectwinner, "expected to win","expected to lose")))%>%
  mutate(outcome = ifelse(winner=="tie", "tie", ifelse(expectflag=="too close", "too close", ifelse(expectflag=="expected to win", ifelse(winner==expectwinner, "win as expected", "unexpected loss"), ifelse(expectflag=="expected to lose", ifelse(winner==expectwinner, "lost as expected", "unexpected win"), "")))))
  
   #mutate(outcome =  ifelse(winner==expectwinner, "expected", ifelse(tiegame=="tie", "tie", ifelse(teamname==expectwinner, "unexpected loss","unexpected win"))))%>%
  
elo_teams$winflag <- "NA"
elo_teams$winflag[elo_teams$outcome=="tie"] <- "tie"
elo_teams$winflag[elo_teams$winner==elo_teams$teamname] <- "win"
elo_teams$winflag[elo_teams$winner!=elo_teams$teamname] <- "loss"
elo_teams%>%group_by(expectflag, outcome)%>%summarise(count=n())
elo_teams%>%filter(teamname=="MIN")%>%select(teamname, winner, expectwinner, expectflag, tm1, tm2, score1, score2, outcome)
#analysis
#teams by playoff games
playoffs <- elo_teams%>%filter(season>="1966", playoff!="NA", score1!="NA")
playoffs2 <- playoffs%>%filter(expectflag=="expected to win")%>%group_by(teamname, outcome)%>%summarise(count=n())%>%mutate(pct=(count/sum(count))*100)%>%mutate(totalgames=sum(count))
playoffs_30games <- playoffs2%>%filter(outcome=="unexpected loss", totalgames>=30)%>%arrange(desc(pct))
print("All playoff games - pct of unexpected losses by team")
[1] "All playoff games - pct of unexpected losses by team"

playoffs_allgames <- playoffs2%>%filter(outcome=="unexpected loss") %>%arrange(desc(pct))
playoffs_allgames$teamname <- factor(playoffs_allgames$teamname, levels = playoffs_allgames$teamname[order(playoffs_allgames$pct)])
playoffs_allgames_chart <- ggplot(playoffs_allgames, aes(x = teamname, y = pct)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", color="black", fill="#59A897") +
    geom_text(stat="identity", label=paste0(round(playoffs_allgames$pct,0), "%"))+
    coord_flip() +
  labs(title = "Pct of playoff games unexpectedly lost", 
       subtitle = "NFL - all playoff games since 1966",
       caption = "Star Tribune graphic by MaryJo Webster",
       x="Team",
       y="Pct games lost unexpectedly")
